# Project: wxSudoku
# Author: Cody Precord
# License: wxWindows

wxSudoku is a simple sudoku game that comes with over 3000 different puzzles.

# Introduction / Rules

Reference: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sudoku

Sudoku is a logic-based number placement puzzle. The objective is to fill a 9×9
grid so that each column, each row, and each of the nine 3×3 boxes (also called
blocks or regions) contains the digits from 1 to 9 only one time each. The
puzzle setter provides a partially completed grid.

# Game Play

Playing wxSudoku is done by clicking on and selecting an empty square and
entering a digit. This continues until all squares are filled with the correct
digits.

# Controls

Mouse Left Button: Select Square
Left Arrow:        Move selection square left
Right Arrow:       Move selection square right
Up Arrow:          Move selection square up
Down Arrow:        Move seelction square down
Number Keys:       Enter Digit 1-9
Backspace:         Clear digit from selected square
Delete:            Clear digit from selected square

# Requirements

python 2.4 or higher
wxPython 2.8+

